The Sheriffs Act 1887 is an Act of the Parliament of the United Kingdom. It sets out the appointments and qualifications of Sheriffs in England and Wales.[4] The Act gives sheriffs the right to arrest those resisting a warrant (posse comitatus). Acts of the Parliament of Scotland
